<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,632,960]" box="[151,276,632,658]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,632,960]" box="[151,418,675,701]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Wingspan: 
<quantity box="[284,413,675,701]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="15.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="14.0">14–16 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,632,960]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Transverse lines: brown, suffused with black scales; antemedial and postmedial lines well marked, with a black spot on costa; subterminal line indistinct.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,632,960]" box="[151,597,805,831]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Reniform: indistinct, almost invisible.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,632,960]" box="[151,366,848,874]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Hindwing: brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,632,960]" box="[151,515,891,917]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Underside: unicolorous brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,632,960]" box="[151,1364,934,960]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Abdomen: brown with black crest dorsally on first segment; male with long black and brown anal tufts.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1435,1020,1606]" box="[151,327,1020,1046]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Male genitalia.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1435,1020,1606]" box="[151,425,1063,1089]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Saccus: short, rounded.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1435,1020,1606]" box="[151,348,1106,1132]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Vinculum: short.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1435,1020,1606]" box="[151,459,1149,1175]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Tegumen: extremely long.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1435,1020,1606]" box="[151,508,1193,1219]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Tergite and sternite: indistinct.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1435,1020,1606]" box="[151,1023,1236,1262]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Sacculus: with heavily sclerotised cone-like process dorsally on right side.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1435,1020,1606]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Ampulla: asymmetrical, club-like, apically smoothly rounded; on left side a short mushroom-like process. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2007" box="[151,230,1322,1348]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Pollex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pollex</taxonomicName>
: short, rounded, with long hair-like setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1435,1020,1606]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Digitus: on right side, long, narrow, bent, pointed apically; short, stout, tapered, and thorn-like on left side. Juxta: higher than wide.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1435,1020,1606]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Anellus: fused with juxta, dorsally membranous on left side, forming almost a full circle around phallus. Fultura superior: membranous.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1435,1020,1606]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Phallus: broadest by ductus ejaculatorius, coiling clock-wise, S-shaped, slight tapering towards apex; coecum long and narrow.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1667,2037]" box="[151,353,1667,1693]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Female genitalia.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1667,2037]" box="[151,452,1710,1736]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Ovipositor: quadrangular.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1667,2037]" box="[151,900,1753,1779]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Anterior apophyses: length equal to that of posterior apophyses.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1667,2037]" box="[151,966,1793,1822]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
8 
<superScript attach="left" box="[165,177,1793,1807]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">th</superScript>
abdominal segment: very narrow, ventrally fused with 7 
<superScript attach="left" box="[841,853,1793,1807]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">th</superScript>
segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1667,2037]" box="[151,1234,1836,1865]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
7 
<superScript attach="left" box="[165,177,1836,1850]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">th</superScript>
abdominal segment: heavily sclerotised, anteriorly with an irregular, triangular extension.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1667,2037]" box="[151,658,1882,1908]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Antrum: short, tapered, heavily sclerotised.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1667,2037]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Ductus bursae: membranous, long, coiling by antrum; ostium and ductus bursae 2 X as long as corpus bursae. Appendix bursae: arising postteriorly from ductus bursae immediately after antrum.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1667,2037]" box="[151,438,2011,2037]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Corpus bursae: globular.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,158,270]" box="[151,412,158,184]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,158,270]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
The female genitalia resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2007" box="[621,710,201,226]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Tolpia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fyani">
<emphasis box="[621,710,201,226]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">T. fyani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differ in the shape of ostium and the irregular, triangular extension of the 7 
<superScript attach="left" box="[360,372,241,255]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">th</superScript>
segment.
</paragraph>
